  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6586.74 sitting below the 6598 flip point in a strong PIN regime, dealers are currently net buying the dip as their long gamma positioning dictates. The massive +94.6B gamma wall at 6600 creates a powerful magnetic effect just 13 points above current levels, while the thick cluster of positive gamma from 6590-6610 forms a consolidation zone that should contain price action. The recent GEX surge reinforces dealer stabilization flows, with the 6560 negative gamma level acting as a potential acceleration point if breached to the downside.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect SPX to grind higher toward 6600 with dealers providing buying support on any weakness.",
